07\/23\/new-moon-begins-ends-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":38837,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: New moon begins and ends Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not fast the month of Ramadan until you see the crescent moon, and do not break your fast until you see it. If the sky is cloudy for you, then estimate it.\u201d In another narration, the Prophet\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3969,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/01\/signs-hour-boast-masjid\/","url_meta":{"origin":38837,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Masajid: People will boast about their mosques","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe Hour will not be established until people boast about their mosques.\" Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 449 Grade: \u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0648\u0645\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0639\u064e\u0629\u064f \u062d\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u064a\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0647\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0633